Globally celebrated singer, Davido has decried the rise in the dollar to naira exchange rate. The Afrobeats star tweeted  that dollar to naira exchange rate is heading to N1,000 to a $1 if the rise persists. The “Stand Strong” singer insisted drastic action must be taken to forestall such ‘doomsday’ reality.   How Nigerian men define strong women, by Toke Makinwa     11 celebrity couples that make marriage look beautiful     Why leaders are not bothered about out-of-school children…   Read Also: My next album will bring original Davido back, says singer “Dollar heading to 1k. drastic action is needed,” Davido tweeted. As reported in NaijaNews on May 31, 2022, the exchange rate for a dollar to naira at Lagos Parallel Market (Black Market), players buy a dollar for N580 and sell at N610 on Monday, 30th May, according to sources at Bureau De Change (BDC).